<h2>Overview</h2><p>Installing an aftermarket skid plate is a significant upgrade for anyone looking to enhance their Jeep's off-road capabilities while ensuring vital components are protected. Today, we delve into the installation of the <strong>Rock Hard 4X4 Evap Skid (RH-6005)</strong>, specifically designed for Jeep Wrangler JK models from 2007 to 2018. This upgrade is not just about aesthetics; it’s a crucial step to safeguard your vehicle's evaporative emissions system.</p><h2>What This Covers</h2><p>This article outlines the quick and easy process for installing the Rock Hard 4X4 Evap Skid. We will go through the necessary tools, provide a step-by-step installation guide, and highlight the key features that make this skid plate a top choice for Jeep enthusiasts.</p><h2>Step-by-Step Breakdown</h2><p>Before you begin, ensure you have the following tools on hand:</p><ul><li>13mm socket wrench</li><li>Torque wrench</li><li>Angle grinder (optional, for removing the factory skid)</li><li>Paint (optional, for customization)</li></ul><p>1. <strong>Remove the Factory Skid Plate:</strong> Begin by unbolting the factory EVAP skid plate. You'll typically find it secured with four bolts—two in the front, one at the back, and a lower connection beneath. It’s advisable to unfasten the undercoating carefully and lower the existing plate.</p><p>2. <strong>Prepare the Area:</strong> If your model has any custom elements like an exhaust modification, ensure these are noted before removing components.</p><p>3. <strong>Install the Rock Hard Skid:</strong> Position the new skid over the same mounting points as your original plate. Fit the first bolt at the back, then secure the front bolts. The Rock Hard 4X4 system comes with alignment protrusions which help stabilize the installation.</p><p>4. <strong>Tighten Everything Down:</strong> Once securely in place, use a torque wrench to fasten the bolts to recommended specifications.</p><p>5. <strong>Final Adjustments:</strong> Don’t forget to reattach any exhaust hangers or additional components, and ensure everything is snug and secure.</p><h2>Helpful Tips</h2><p>While the installation process is straightforward, here are some tips to make the experience smoother:</p><ul><li>Consider painting your skid plate to match your Jeep's aesthetic—Rust-Oleum’s automotive epoxy paint works wonders and adds a unique touch.</li><li>Keep in mind safety throughout the installation. When using tools like the angle grinder, ensure you are wearing appropriate personal protective equipment.</li><li>If you encounter any resistance, be patient. Sometimes, these factory parts can be tougher to remove than anticipated.</li></ul><h2>Key Takeaways</h2><p>Upgrading to the Rock Hard 4X4 Evap Skid for your Jeep Wrangler JK is undoubtedly an investment in the longevity and performance of your vehicle. Its robust 3/16” thick steel construction and straightforward installation process are tailored for even the most novice DIY enthusiast. The sleek black powder coat finish doesn't just make it look sharp; it also adds a layer of corrosion resistance. With a lifetime warranty and its made-in-USA designation, this skid plate is a purchase you can feel confident about. Don’t leave your EVAP canister exposed on rugged terrain. Install the Rock Hard 4X4 Evap Skid now and hit the trails with peace of mind!</p>

